<TITLE> SC declares 450 Rajuk job cuts illegal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court upheld Monday the High Court verdict that termination of 450 Rajuk staff was illegal. A full bench of the Appellate Division led by chief justice MM Ruhul Amin delivered the ruling, quashing 39 leave-to-appeals of city development authority Rajuk against the High Court verdict. The public works ministry had terminated their service in several phases beginning Feb 18, 2004. Rajuk surveyor Ashutosh Chakma, MLSS Nurul Islam, junior account assistant Abdul Mabub and others challenged their job termination orders. The High Court delivered verdict on their writ petitions on June 5-6, 2007. Rajuk later filed leave to appeals with the Supreme Court
